- What.

597
00:33:03,775 --> 00:33:06,436
Casey said that you had a great time

598
00:33:06,899 --> 00:33:09,068
on our first date.
Was she telling the truth ?

599
00:33:10,317 --> 00:33:11,317
Yeah.

600
00:33:12,019 --> 00:33:14,619
- Well, I mean, sort of...
- Clearly not.

601
00:33:15,734 --> 00:33:17,066
She convinced you how ?

602
00:33:17,191 --> 00:33:18,900
Did she express pity for me ?

603
00:33:19,025 --> 00:33:21,821
Appeal to your sense of charity ?
She belittle my chocolate fondue,

604
00:33:21,946 --> 00:33:23,984
because I could tell
she thought it was lame.

605
00:33:24,109 --> 00:33:26,409
Casey loves fondue.
She really likes you, too.

606
00:33:26,964 --> 00:33:29,070
But... you don't ?

607
00:33:29,195 --> 00:33:31,213
I do, and I'll prove it to you.

608
00:33:31,338 --> 00:33:33,482
I'll tell her that I don't
want her car.

609
00:33:33,679 --> 00:33:35,284
She bribed you with her car ?

610
00:33:35,409 --> 00:33:37,500
Am I that pathetic ?
And what are you ?

611
00:33:37,625 --> 00:33:40,156
Some brother-whore to be bought
and traded like a commodity ?

612
00:33:40,353 --> 00:33:41,518
Casey, hi. Great !

613
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:45,161
Did you offer your car to Rusty
to date me so we could be friends ?

614
00:33:45,358 --> 00:33:47,691
- Katherine, look, I thought...
- I need to breathe.

615
00:33:48,945 --> 00:33:51,541
I wanted us to be friends
because I respect and admire you.

616
00:33:51,666 --> 00:33:53,812
- And I just want you to be happy.
- Me, too.

617
00:33:53,937 --> 00:33:56,908
Forget about what brought us here.
Just think about what is going on now.

618
00:33:57,078 --> 00:33:58,228
I'm thinking.

619
00:33:59,914 --> 00:34:02,664
Why don't you just give me one
reason why I should forgive you.

620
00:34:03,917 --> 00:34:04,792
Heads up !

621
00:34:05,218 --> 00:34:06,168
My gosh !

622
00:34:13,023 --> 00:34:16,010
First a fire, now this. Katherine's
gonna think we're trying to kill her.

623
00:34:16,564 --> 00:34:19,723
- Are you ?
- I'm the one she's going to hate.

624
00:34:19,896 --> 00:34:21,974
Just when I think I kinda like her.

625
00:34:22,099 --> 00:34:23,060
Really ?

626
00:34:24,438 --> 00:34:26,313
- What are you doing here ?
- Drama, Rus.

627
00:34:26,481 --> 00:34:28,981
Had to bring Bridget in.
There was a...

628
00:34:29,346 --> 00:34:30,296
accident.

629
00:34:31,475 --> 00:34:33,125
Involving her retainer.

630
00:34:33,777 --> 00:34:37,116
She's gonna be fine
but I'm gonna need some stitches.

631
00:34:39,953 --> 00:34:41,245
Thank God !
You're OK !

632
00:34:41,413 --> 00:34:43,121
"Tis only a flesh wound".

633
00:34:43,290 --> 00:34:44,707
Monty Python.
That's funny.

634
00:34:44,888 --> 00:34:46,834
"We are the Knights who say Ni".

635
00:34:47,210 --> 00:34:50,463
I've got you on strong pain killers.
A good thing the arrow was blunt-tipped

636
00:34:50,588 --> 00:34:52,797
or you'd be spending Valentine's Day
in the morgue.

637
00:34:52,966 --> 00:34:54,383
